description.narrative: (Haiti): .Evaluation and Survey Services (ESS) is a monitoring and evaluation platform contract used to design and carry out evaluation activities to support stronger results and to improve evidence-based programming. These efforts will facilitate informed program management decisions, shape the long-term strategic direction of Mission programs, and assess the results of ongoing activities. FY 2020 funds will be used to carry out various performance evaluations of several activities implemented within the economic growth, governance, agriculture, education and health sectors. Using FY2020 funding, ESS will continue with the impact evaluation of the Mission's early grade reading program started in FY 2017, conduct the midterm evaluations of the Project Supporting the Efficient Management of State Resources (GERE) and the Community Driven Development (CDD) project. ESS will also implement five (5) final performance evaluations among which the final evaluation of the RANFOSE, AKSYON, SANTE, JSSP and CEPPs Activities and two (2) baseline surveys: one for the Education Strong Beginning Activity and one for the DO2 Resilience Program currently under design. ESS will also start building monitoring and evaluation capacity among USAID, local research firms and consultants to enable them to use monitoring and evaluation data to support adaptive management in line with USAID policy, international standards, and best practices..
